        .featured-collection
          a href='/collections/925'
            img.expimg src="#{asset_path('explore/pacifica.jpg')}"
            h5 Pacifica Radio Archives
          p.explorep 
            | Pacifica's world renowned archives include collections such as
            a href="https://www.popuparchive.org/search?page=1&query=tag:%22American%20Women%20Making%20History%20and%20Culture:%201963-1982%22"  American Women Making History and Culture
            | , featuring interviews like Yoko Ono and Anais Nin, and 
            a href="https://www.popuparchive.com/collections/1686" Pacifica Grammy
            | , featuring digitized radio dramas and rare concerts from the 1960s and 1970s.
        .featured-collection
          a href='/collections/583' 
            img.expimg src="#{asset_path('explore/WILL.jpg')}"
            h5 Illinois Public Radio
          p.explorep  
            | Illinois Public Radio, public broadcasting for central Illinois, captured the voices from inside America's biggest social movements of the 20th century. Listen to the original rhetoric that drove 
            a href="https://www.popuparchive.com/search?page=1&sortBy=_score&sortOrder=desc&query=tag:%22African%20American%20Civil%20Rights%22" civil rights
            |, 
            a href="https://www.popuparchive.com/search?page=1&sortBy=date_added&sortOrder=desc&query=%22Women%27s%20Rights%22,collection_id:%22583-Illinois%20Public%20Media%22" second-wave feminism
            |, and reform and equality in 
            a href="https://www.popuparchive.com/search?page=1&sortBy=date_added&sortOrder=desc&query=collection_id:%22583-Illinois%20Public%20Media%22,tag:%22Public%20Education%22" education
            |.
